  "response": "Yes, many middle-class people shop at thrift stores. Thrift stores often offer a wide variety of affordable clothing, furniture, home goods, and other items that appeal to budget-conscious shoppers, regardless of income level. Additionally, some people enjoy the thrill of finding unique or vintage items, and shopping at thrift stores can also be a more sustainable and environmentally friendly option. Thrift shopping has become increasingly popular in recent years, crossing socioeconomic lines and attracting a diverse range of customers.",
